Merkel’s Coalition to Close Eight Nuclear Plants, Leipziger Says

-- B y   T o n y   C z u c z k a
-- 
2011-04-01T06:17:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-01/merkel-s-coalition-to-close-eight-nuclear-plants-leipziger-says.html
Chancellor Angela Merkel’s coalition
has agreed to seek the closure of eight of  Germany ’s 17 nuclear
power plants, the Leipziger Volkszeitung reported, citing
unidentified coalition officials.  The three coalition parties plan to propose legislation
with revised safety standards that ensure the nation’s seven
pre-1980s reactors and the Kruemmel plant will shut down, the
 newspaper  said in an e-mailed copy of an article today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tony Czuczka in Berlin at 
 aczuczka@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at   jhertling@bloomberg.net  